The paper focuses on a natural language processing task of action-graph extraction from material science papers. This task falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach involves training a learning agent to execute the procedure correctly in a text-based simulated lab environment, which requires machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses potential limitations and advantages of the approach, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
